<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.5151/334: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Philip</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-30T15:00:00-04:00">June 30, 1936—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 3:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>60. Referring to previous correspondence respecting our exchange
                            difficulties with Chile, I strongly advise that no further action be
                            taken by the Department until after the completion and receipt of the
                            study of the entire question now in preparation by the Commercial
                            Attaché.</p>
                        <p>The shortage of dollar and pound exchange in this market is most acute
                            and I think that no advantage would be derived from further official
                            emphasis by us at this juncture.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Philip</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>